  "text": "It has been demonstrated that coupled mode theory can model the behaviour of light in a system of interacting resonant and propagating modes [CITATION_1] . We use this approach to model our dynamic Q control device (Fig. 5) . This model simulates the amplitude of the field in the resonator, c, as it interacts with the field amplitude of propagating modes in the waveguide coming and going from a left port (S l± ) and right port (S r± ): ",
